SOOTY PAINT
-----------

Loading


IBM PC - Type paint at the DOS prompt.

AMIGA  - Insert Disk at the disk loading screen

Printer Setup
-------------

Please follow on screen instructions if you should wish to use a printer.

Colouring.
==========

You can "paint" up to 45 pictures of Sooty and friends. Using the mouse
click on either of the arrows displayed at the bottom of the screen to move
to the picture you wish to paint. Clicking on a colour, then simply put the
mouse pointer on the area you wish to paint and click. You can change the
colour tones by clicking on the CHANGE COLOUR box and then moving the Red,
Green and Blue slide controls, using your mouse just click on OK when you
are happy. You can MIX colours by clicking on the mix button at the top of
the screen and then click on the second colour you wish to mix. If you click
on ERASE then your last action will be removed.

Skip option.
============

You can skip any picture by pressing this button. Once pressed a requester
will appear with four buttons, +, -, OK and CANCEL. Use + and - to
increase/decrease the Picture number then press OK to go to that picture or
CANCEL to return to the current picture.

Printing
========

If you can click on PRINT then you will have the option to print out the
picture if required.

Printer Screen
==============

Select the type of print by clicking on the buttons. If you want to print
out a calendar, set up the month and year that is required by clicking on
the + & - icons next to year and month. When you are happy with your
choice, click on PRINT otherwise click on CANCEL. If your printer is not
on line, then you get a message saying "PRINTER OFF LINE", if this happens
click on OK abd set-up your printer, once your printer is set-up correctly,
click on PRINT again.

Printer Options
===============

        
PRINT PICTURE. This will print the picture on its own.

PRINT MESSAGE.
        This will print the picture with up to three lines of text above
        and below.

PRINT BANNER.
        This will print the Picture with a line of text above and below.

PRINT CALENDAR.
        This will print the picture with a calendar for any month of the
        year.

PRINT CARD.
        This will print the picture with either Happy Christmas or Happy
        Birthday with a name. By Clicking on STOP you can exit from the
        game.

DRAWING.
========

If you select the DRAW at the top of the screen, any line drawing will be
removed and lost. By clicking on the boxes at the bottom of the screen you
can draw squares, circles, ovals, triangles, straight lines, dots and free
line styles. There is also a RUB OUT option. Once you are happy with your
drawing you can then colour it in by selecting PAINT.

